    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if the pH is too high it's basically just stuck in the ground? i was looking at the soil under the bushes and it looks really dense and dark, almost like stuff is being moved around down there. is it common for the soil structure to change or for things to get compacted in a way that affects how the roots reach the nutrients?",
